  "slug": "faggots",
  "title": "Faggots",
  "subtitle": "Pork and liver meatballs baked in a dark onion gravy",
  "excerpt": "Faggots are meatballs made from minced pork and liver, bound with breadcrumbs and seasoned with sage and mace. They are baked in a rich onion gravy until the tops are dark and the gravy is thick. This is a dish of the Midlands and South Wales, resolutely unfashionable and deeply good.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Traditional British Midlands and South Wales. Mrs Beeton's Book of Household Management (1861) documents force-meat balls from offal in the same tradition. Welsh faggots are traditionally wrapped in caul fat. Mr Brain's Faggots became a twentieth-century factory product from the same tradition.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Faggots",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpdr526i0000lwv4i8zc2ljo"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " are made from the cheaper parts of the pig: liver and belly or mince, stretched with breadcrumbs. They are not subtle. The sage and mace are strong, the gravy is dark, and the liver flavour is unmistakeable. Served with mushy peas and mashed potato, they are one of the most satisfying things you can make from inexpensive ingredients.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Traditional recipes wrap each faggot in ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "caul fat",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpdr52790001lwv4q12chttj"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " before baking. If you can get it from a butcher, use it; the faggots will be moister and hold their shape more cleanly. Without it, chilling the formed faggots for 30 minutes before baking achieves a similar result.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
