      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the faggots",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mince the liver finely or pulse in a food processor until fine but not smooth. Combine with the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{pork-mince}} of pork mince",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": ", ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{lard}} of lard",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": ", ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{breadcrumbs-fresh}} of breadcrumbs",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": ", 1 grated onion, ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{sage}} of chopped sage",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": ", ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{mace}}",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": ", ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{sea-salt-flakes}}",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " and ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{black-pepper}}",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": ". Mix thoroughly. The mixture will be soft. Divide into 8 equal portions and roll into balls. Place on a plate, cover, and refrigerate for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the onion gravy and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{olive-oil}} of olive oil",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " in a large roasting pan over medium heat. Fry the 2 sliced onions for 15 minutes until deeply golden. Stir in ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{plain-flour}} of flour",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " and cook for 1 minute. Add ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{stock-beef}} of beef stock",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " and the Worcestershire sauce if using. Stir until smooth and bring to a simmer. Nestle the cold faggots into the gravy. Transfer to a 180°C oven and bake uncovered for 40-45 minutes until the tops are dark brown and the gravy has reduced and thickened. Rest for 5 minutes before serving.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "rows": [
            {
              "fix": "Add an extra 20 g of breadcrumbs to the mixture. Chill the formed faggots for at least 30 minutes; the fat firms up and holds them together.",
              "cause": "Mixture was too wet, or not chilled long enough before baking",
              "symptom": "Faggots fall apart in the gravy"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Process the liver until very fine. The ratio of 400g liver to 300g pork can be adjusted to 300g liver and 400g pork for a milder result.",
              "cause": "The liver was not minced finely enough, or too high a proportion of liver to pork",
              "symptom": "Liver flavour is too strong"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Bake uncovered and allow the gravy to reduce. If still thin, transfer the faggots to a serving dish, reduce the gravy by simmering on the hob, and pour over.",
              "cause": "Too much stock, or the lid was left on during baking",
              "symptom": "Gravy is thin and watery"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Faggots are done at 40 minutes. The lard is important: it keeps the inside moist during baking.",
              "cause": "Overcooked, or too little fat in the mixture",
              "symptom": "Faggots are dry inside"
            }
          ]
        },
        "content": []
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Faggots belong to the Midlands and South Wales, where they were made on pig-killing day using liver, heart, and belly trimmings that could not be stored. They are eaten with mushy peas, chips, and thick gravy. The factory product (Mr Brain's) made them a national convenience food in the twentieth century, but the homemade version bears almost no resemblance to the frozen one.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
